    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-04-09T03:34:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-04-09T03:34:00-05:00" n="691"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d691">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.77/1457: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Harbin</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Jenkins</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Harbin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-04-09T17:00:00+08:26">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 9, 1920—5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received April 10—2:26 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>General Horvat left to-day for Peking, announcement being he is on leave absence.
                    Pimenoff, manager of the Russo-Asiatic Bank will act as manager of the railway
                    during Horvat’s absence. Horvat will undoubtedly take up railway situation with
                    Peking authorities.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Jenkins</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
